Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.88,0:00:29.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Here comes the pain! {Not too sure about this line, but not sure what to suggest. "Here comes the pain train!" seems too silly and is almost certainly too loose. Leave it as-is if it seems fine to you. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.63,0:00:31.84,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Take this! And that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:34.22,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Seriously! \N Who do you think you are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.22,0:00:35.76,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Fucking loser!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:48.77,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Oh, he dropped something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.40,0:00:50.73,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.07,0:00:54.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mario Zucchero.\N From Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.07,0:00:56.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So he's a thug{Note that he does not say "gyangu" here so do NOT change this to "gangster" -Starfish} from Rome...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.75,0:01:07.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That a piece of garbage stuck to your face?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.21,0:01:10.30,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Or is it just seaweed?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.30,0:01:15.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Sure {\i1}looks{\i0} like seaweed, \Nbut it could be plastic, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:24.14,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Would break my heart if it was garbage. \N That'd mean this beautiful ocean's polluted.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:27.23,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Mind if I take a closer look?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:29.44,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.27,0:01:33.36,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I asked if it was okay to take a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.36,0:01:38.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Least you could do is\Nanswer a simple question, asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:42.20,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Capri...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.20,0:01:47.12,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,When the ancient Greeks colonized\N various lands throughout the Mediterranean Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.12,0:01:51.71,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...they sought out the most \N beautiful places in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:54.88,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Among those colonized lands was Capri.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.88,0:01:57.43,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The blue sea, the sparkling sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:04.31,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,In stark contrast to the beautiful scenery, the shoreline is \Nmade up of sheer white cliffs, giving it a fortress-like appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:11.56,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,While the Roman Empire reigned, an emperor vacationed there,\N only returning to Rome after ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:20.53,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Bruno Buccellati and his team are about to reach the island \Nin order to lay claim to Polpo's hidden fortune of ten billion lire. {"about to reach the island" looks weird to me. Literal is more like they are about to MAKE LANDFALL on the island. -Starfish}{both phrases are functionally the same, just that making landfall is the technical description. I don't feel this needs to change. -JMFW}
