Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:04:00.84,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Buccellati, we should set course for land soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:05.97,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I've been on the lookout for some time, \Nand there doesn't seem to be any boats following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:10.22,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No one should be aware that \N this boat is headed to Capri. {Hmm... I guess this MIGHT be good but I kinda feel like this phrasing almost sounds more like a "It's important that nobody know this boat is headed to Capri" when the Japanese is more "I don't think there's anyway anyone could realize that this boat is headed to Capri." -Starfish}{Maybe "be aware that" in place of "know"? - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:12.94,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Yeah, there aren't any boats around, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.94,0:04:16.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm worried about how he \N learned of Polpo's hidden fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:20.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I just can't accept that he chose\N to follow us on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:28.33,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I noticed you eyeing these earlier, \Nbut they're not mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:30.54,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,They were inside the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:34.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Which one do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.17,0:04:36.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The glasses or the fishing line?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.17,0:04:39.96,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We need answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:43.55,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're gonna be in deep shit\N if you don't start talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.55,0:04:46.72,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You working with someone, Mr. Zucchero?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:49.64,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Probably a Stand user too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.39,0:04:52.39,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That's why I'm using these.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:55.90,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You sure you don't got a preference?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.90,0:04:58.61,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If you're not gonna choose...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.44,0:05:03.82,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...I'll just have to use both!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.91,0:05:11.33,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Well? Feel like talking now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.33,0:05:16.42,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Ma-ri-o Zuc-che-ro. \NHeaven, Hell, or the Ninth Circle of Hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:17.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Heaven, Hell, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.58,0:05:20.04,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,The Ninth Circle of Hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.88,0:05:25.09,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,His name reading says he's going \Nstraight to the Ninth Circle of Hell! {Jules please think of something else for the love of god. -J}{Best I can think of "My little game" or something to that effect. - Toa}{what was this even about lol. if i objected previously, i was probably being a dum -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.97,0:06:20.69,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If you're not gonna tell us \Nyour partner's name or what their Stand does...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.69,0:06:27.65,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...then I'd start worrying about \Nthat other eye of yours, Mr. Zucchero!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:30.28,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Quit fucking around!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.28,0:06:33.12,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Jesus. Get over here and look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:35.58,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,He was using the boat radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.62,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I presume you found something\N with Moody Blues' replay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:40.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:46.34,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The boat was flat at the time, but now that it's back to normal, \N we should be able to see this in three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.39,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.39,0:06:58.23,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You're still not allowed to see my Stand. {meanie}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:06:59.44,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:07:02.40,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'll do you a favor and let you listen in. {This also applies to Abbacchio peeing. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.11,0:07:10.03,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,While I was watching the replay, \Nhe started using the radio in the cabin below us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:11.49,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,He contacted someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.11,0:07:14.45,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,I already took four of 'em as hostages.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.45,0:07:17.24,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,Only Buccellati and another guy are left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:19.12,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,I'll be done here in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:21.08,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,They were goin'...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:22.67,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,...to Capri!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.42,0:07:28.05,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,{\an8}Didn't hear 'em say where the money's at, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.71,0:07:26.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, what are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:28.05,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He told someone where we're headed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.05,0:07:33.26,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,Once I eliminate his friends,\N I'm gonna make Buccellati cough up the location. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:37.26,Narrator,Sale,0,0,0,,Was their yacht the Lagoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.26,0:07:39.02,Narrator,Sale,0,0,0,,Whereabouts are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.02,0:07:42.23,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,About two hours from Capri.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:48.15,Main,Mario,0,0,0,,Buccellati's afraid of bein' tailed, \Nso he's takin' the long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:50.32,Narrator,Sale,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.99,Narrator,Sale,0,0,0,,I'll take a speedboat and wait for you at Capri.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.99,0:07:56.28,Narrator,Sale,0,0,0,,Dock at Marina Grande. \N Over and out. {https://www.capri.net/en/s/marina-grande-2}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:02.21,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The conversation ends there. \NThe radio cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.83,0:08:04.00,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,How could this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:08.13,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,This is awful! He could go from Naples \N to Capri in thirty minutes with a speedboat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:11.30,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's already on the island for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.30,0:08:14.89,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Who was that? \NWho was he talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.89,0:08:20.02,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I won't stop 'til this guy\N coughs up his buddy's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:23.60,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No, he's a hardcore gangster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:26.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Odds are it will take too long \Nto get any good info out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:28.98,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I doubt we would get anywhere today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.98,0:08:32.78,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Besides, he may not even know \Nwhat his partner's Stand is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:36.12,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,There's a good chance he chose to\N keep it a secret even from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.12,0:08:37.78,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So what can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.78,0:08:40.16,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We'll never make it to port\N without getting spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.16,0:08:44.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If he figures out we're the ones \N driving the boat and not Zucchero...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:49.17,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Not to mention if it doesn't arrive\Nat Marina Grande in about an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:54.18,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,...the man on the radio will \Nrealize something happened to Zucchero!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:57.30,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Will we still be able to get \Nthe money if that happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:08:58.10,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Worse yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:01.72,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,...we may not even make it back\N to Naples alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.85,0:09:06.23,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,What's the plan, Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.73,0:09:11.65,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,We can't wait on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:14.90,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Our best bet is to catch him off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.90,0:09:16.61,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,We have to beat him there somehow... {this is long for the time on screen..."get there" instead of "reach the island"? think we can afford to be generic here. also given context, why would Bruno say "I" here? He's maintained that *someone*, any one of them, needs to get to the island before the rest of the team.  -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.61,0:09:18.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Before the boat reaches port...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:28.04,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...one of us needs to head \N to the island and eliminate him. {thanks for reading the Bucc's mind, GioGio}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.04,0:09:32.25,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You hearing yourself right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:35.09,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You sure you're not retarded?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.09,0:09:37.59,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Get to the island before the boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:39.80,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You planning to {\i1}swim{\i0} there or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:40.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.55,0:09:41.31,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:44.77,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I can imbue this lifesaver \N with the life of a fish. {OOOOCEAN MAN TAKE ME BY THE HAND}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.77,0:09:49.15,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If it pulls me along,\N I'll reach the island faster than the yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:53.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,And naturally, since it's my Stand,\N I'll be the one going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.57,0:09:59.41,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I, Giorno Giovanna, have a dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.41,0:10:01.62,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I want to obtain that ten billion lire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.62,0:10:04.58,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We need that money to ensure\N Buccellati becomes a capo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:09.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...so that we can move up in the ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:10.75,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.84,0:10:20.05,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,You wanna go? Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:22.51,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Not a bad idea, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:26.60,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Too bad you don't have a clue \N who this guy is or what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:30.06,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Capri is flooded with tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.06,0:10:32.52,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,How the hell do you think you'll find him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:35.65,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I gotta side with Giorno on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:39.24,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Even though I have no idea who this guy is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:44.83,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If he's waiting for Zucchero \Nto get there in this boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:49.54,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...I think we have \N a good shot at striking first...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:53.71,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...before he can strike at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.01,0:11:00.34,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So how many people can \Nthat fish of yours pull, Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.18,0:11:06.89,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,My Stand, Sex Pistols, \N specializes in assassinations. {jules gieb thots -J}{Literally "specializes in assassinations." -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:13.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's perfect for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:15.65,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Let's go get him!{Literally "I'm coming with you!" -Starfish}
Comment: 0,0:11:18.03,0:11:18.07,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:37.17,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I didn't expect it would take this long \N to reach the island from the yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:42.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We have twenty minutes before Zucchero \N said he would meet with the man on Capri.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.47,0:11:44.80,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We can't take much longer than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.80,0:11:47.26,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno, how's the marina look?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.93,0:11:50.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.56,0:11:54.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Like Abbacchio said, it's full of tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.48,0:11:57.40,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Several seem to be waiting for someone. {Kinda wanna suggest "A number" but that'd lengthen an already CPS-heavy line. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.98,0:12:02.11,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,They're probably just waiting \N for sightseeing vessels, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.66,0:12:09.75,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mista, you have a plan for finding the mystery man \N in the next twenty minutes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.13,0:12:25.97,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:32.39,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We're way overdue for lunch. {typical fucking italian}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.39,0:12:40.44,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'd prefer to eat at one of the restaurants over there, \Nbut having lunch on the marina is probably a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.44,0:12:47.95,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I don't know that guy's face, \Nbut he probably knows mine since I'm on Buccellati's team.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:49.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Yours too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:54.21,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I have no idea what you're talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:55.87,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...but listen, Mista.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:13:01.13,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I know I said we had twenty minutes, \Nbut it could be closer to ten if he's the nervous type.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.13,0:13:02.51,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Possibly not even five.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:05.38,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He may fear something \N happened to Zucchero...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:08.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...and become suspicious if \N the Lagoon doesn't arrive at port on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:11.39,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We'll never find him if that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.39,0:13:12.77,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We need to make our move right{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:14.89,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Like I said, it's time for lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:17.35,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You {\i1}eat lunch{\i0} when it's lunchtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.35,0:13:20.69,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Even boutiques and bookstores honor lunchtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:24.24,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Nobody works unless \N they've had their lunch. {TYPICAL}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.57,0:13:27.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I mean, not saying {\i1}I{\i0} work that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.87,0:13:31.41,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...but unfortunately these little rascals\N like to keep the custom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:34.66,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Lunchtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.66,0:13:35.75,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,I'm starvin'  here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.75,0:13:39.13,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Here you go, fellas! \N Lunch is served!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:41.34,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Tuscan salami is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.55,0:13:45.59,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.59,0:13:46.76,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,So good!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:48.97,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Gimme that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:52.56,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Not this again, Number 3! {dadsta in action}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:55.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Stop making Number 5 cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:57.94,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,And quit fighting.\N There's enough for all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.52,0:14:04.32,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,They all think they do the most work, \Nso naturally they also think they deserve more than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:07.40,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I try {\i1}really{\i0} hard not to play favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.74,0:14:13.99,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Number 5!\N For crying out loud, quit crying!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.66,0:14:16.54,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.54,0:14:18.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,How many of those things do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.42,0:14:20.92,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, they aren't "things"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:23.50,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,They get testy if \N you treat 'em like pets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:24.88,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,There's six in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:28.76,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,No Number 4 since it's bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:31.93,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Each of them clings to a chambered bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.93,0:14:33.18,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Clings to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.18,0:14:36.68,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,My buddy over here is rushing us...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.68,0:14:41.23,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,You guys mind holding off on the nap\N'til after we're done working?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:43.52,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Fat chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.19,0:14:46.15,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Hey, Number 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:48.36,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I told you to stop hitting the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.36,0:14:49.36,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mista!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.36,0:14:52.20,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I'll get 'em ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:53.12,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.49,0:14:56.58,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Go grab the radio out of \N the plastic bag we brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.80,0:15:09.05,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,We get to pig out once the gig's out! {5 points to gryffindor for this}{Fucking love this line -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:10.80,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Up and at 'em, fellas!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.68,0:15:24.27,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Here's the plan: I'm gonna sneak up to \N the watchhouse and stick to the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:32.28,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Is there anyone waiting for\N a yacht called the Lagoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.74,0:15:38.33,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,We received a transmission from\N a Mr. Zucchero on the Lagoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:41.62,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Please come to the boat watchhouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:45.84,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Is there anyone waiting for\N a yacht called the Lagoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:51.13,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}We received a transmission from \N a Mr. Zucchero on the Lagoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:54.30,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Please come to the boat watchhouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:54.30,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,He might decide to play it safe\N and not answer the radio call... {Suggesting "opt" in place of "decide". - Toa}{"opt" doesn't feel very Mista to me but I'll leave it up to Josh -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:16:00.23,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,Or maybe he'll get excited and expose himself, \Nthinking he found the hiding place of the ten billion lire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.23,0:16:07.57,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,It's a gamble, but whoever comes to the boat watchhouse \Nto answer the radio call is our guy.
